OL,3,CHealth improvements for those with
OL,4,Cchronic illness after lifestyle courses
OL,6,FJon says one of the key changes he
OL,7,Fmade was completely cutting
OL,8,F'eradicated' ultra-processed foods
OL,9,Ffrom his diet.
OL,11,FThese foods are usually high in sugar,
OL,12,Funhealthy fats and salt - as well as
OL,13,Fcontaining additives.
OL,15,FSince completing the course, Jo
OL,16,FCarpenter has completely come off her
OL,17,Fblood pressure medicine.
OL,19,FShe says the courses have helped her
OL,20,Fto incorporate healthier foods into
OL,21,Fher diet.
