OL,3,CHealth improvements for those with
OL,4,Cchronic illness after lifestyle courses
OL,6,F"Many common and costly health
OL,7,Fconditions are preventable. Evidence
OL,8,Fshows that by supporting protective
OL,9,Ffactors like improving diet,
OL,10,Fincreasing how active we are and
OL,11,Freducing or stopping smoking and
OL,12,Falcohol use, we can significantly
OL,13,Freduce the likelihood of Islanders
OL,14,Fdeveloping chronic disease."
OL,16,FHe adds that while local providers
OL,17,Fwill be "very important" to the
OL,18,Fprogramme, Public Health must ensure
OL,19,Fthat any services are "fit for purpose
OL,20,Fand offer value for money".
